thread.title: Thai Thitiphun storms first day at Macao Open
thread.title_full: Thai Thitiphun storms first day at Macao Open - The Times of India

author: timesofindia.indiatimes.com
title: Thai Thitiphun storms first day at Macao Open
text:
HONG KONG: Thailand's Thitiphun Chuayprakong stormed past more experienced players to clinch a first round lead at the Venetian Macau Open Thursday with a seven-under-par 64. 

Twenty-three-year-old Thitiphun, who is hoping for his first win on the Asian Tour, took just 29 shots, including eight birdies, to sit atop the leaderboard in the first round at the Macau Golf and Country Club. 

Young Korean Jeunghun Wang and Bangladeshi Siddikur Rahman both finished on 65 while defending champion Anirban Lahiri of India and 2013 winner Scott Hend of Australia were on 66. 

Thai Kiradech Aphibarnrat, who broke into the world's top-50 for the first time in his career this week, battled to a four-under 68 while countryman Thongchai Jaidee came in at 71. South African Ernie Els had a disappointing opening round coming in at 74. 

"Today is a lucky day. I didn't hit it good with my tee shots but I had a good short game. I could make a lot of birdies. This is a great round for me. I'm happy and feel fantastic with a 29 coming in," said Thitiphun. 

Fresh from his Presidents Cup debut where he was disappointed to not deliver a point for the Internationals, Lahiri bounced back in style with a five-birdie round. 

"I think it was a solid round of golf. I misread a few. Hopefully I can make those six or eight footers through the rest of the week," he said. 

Leading scores (par 71) 

64 - Thitiphun Chuayprakong (THA) 

65 - Jeunghun Wang (KOR), Siddikur Rahman (BAN) 

66 - Scott Hend (AUS), Javi Colomo (ESP), Brett Munson (USA), Anirban Lahiri (IND)
